00:08:25.830 --> 00:08:26.735
CHRISTINE MINJI
CHANG: Well, I don't--

00:08:26.735 --> 00:08:27.260
DAWN LEE TU: [INAUDIBLE]

00:08:27.260 --> 00:08:29.300
CHRISTINE MINJI CHANG:
I'm curious-- well,

00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:32.850
one of my examples of how I deal
with diversity in my day-to-day

00:08:32.850 --> 00:08:35.669
life is that there's a
film coming out in August--

00:08:35.669 --> 00:08:38.940
August 17, FYI-- called
"Crazy Rich Asians,"

00:08:38.940 --> 00:08:43.159
and John Chu, who's
from the Bay, as am I,

00:08:43.159 --> 00:08:44.870
he's directing it.

00:08:44.870 --> 00:08:46.290
It's an ensemble
Asian-American--

00:08:46.290 --> 00:08:50.010
it's Asian-- it's actually a
global Asian cast, half of whom

00:08:50.010 --> 00:08:51.150
are Asian-American.

00:08:51.150 --> 00:08:56.250
And recognizing as a
data point, if you will,

00:08:56.250 --> 00:08:59.340
the fact that it's been
"Joy Luck Club," which

00:08:59.340 --> 00:09:02.160
was 25 years ago, was the
last, like, mainstream

00:09:02.160 --> 00:09:05.340
studio-backed ensemble
modern-day Asian-American

00:09:05.340 --> 00:09:08.990
family that was on screen,
it's a big freaking deal

00:09:08.990 --> 00:09:11.100
that it's been 25 years.

00:09:11.100 --> 00:09:12.977
And the fact that
there's the show,

00:09:12.977 --> 00:09:15.060
like, "Fresh Off The Boat"
and Dr. Ken, that there

00:09:15.060 --> 00:09:19.530
are these blips on the radar
about diverse representation

00:09:19.530 --> 00:09:23.010
of Asian-Americans that they
are so heavily weighted in terms

00:09:23.010 --> 00:09:26.280
of the gravity of, like, this
is representing all Asians

00:09:26.280 --> 00:09:27.110
when it's not.

00:09:27.110 --> 00:09:29.060
I mean, everyone
here knows that there

00:09:29.060 --> 00:09:32.040
are more than 46
ethnicities and cultures

00:09:32.040 --> 00:09:34.600
and lang-- like,
way more languages.

00:09:34.600 --> 00:09:38.040
But Asian includes so
many different people.

00:09:38.040 --> 00:09:42.180
And yet people are writing these
individual shows with these

00:09:42.180 --> 00:09:44.640
handful of actors to be,
like, the end-all-be-all

00:09:44.640 --> 00:09:46.170
representatives of diversity.

00:09:46.170 --> 00:09:48.294
That's a lot of pressure.

00:09:48.294 --> 00:09:50.460
It's a lot of excitement,
because diversity suddenly

00:09:50.460 --> 00:09:51.940
matters right now.

00:09:51.940 --> 00:09:54.780
So for me, the way I'm
experiencing it is I'm

00:09:54.780 --> 00:09:56.430
choosing to look
at the positive.

00:09:56.430 --> 00:10:01.110
I'm choosing to look at these
are opportunities and gateways.

00:10:01.110 --> 00:10:03.540
If this movie does
well, and it does matter

00:10:03.540 --> 00:10:06.330
that this movie does well, as
controversial as some people

00:10:06.330 --> 00:10:09.660
might be about this is
just Chinese people,

00:10:09.660 --> 00:10:13.050
and this is just about
Chinese in Singapore,

00:10:13.050 --> 00:10:14.010
did you read the book?

00:10:14.010 --> 00:10:15.780
Like, that's what
the book's about.

00:10:15.780 --> 00:10:19.950
And you cannot in one singular
movie define and represent all

00:10:19.950 --> 00:10:20.850
of Asian-America.

00:10:20.850 --> 00:10:24.330
But still, if this
film does well,

00:10:24.330 --> 00:10:27.270
it does open up doors for
so many other projects

00:10:27.270 --> 00:10:28.500
to get greenlit.

00:10:28.500 --> 00:10:31.020
And Asians do have a
representation in Hollywood.

00:10:31.020 --> 00:10:32.445
And whether this
is true or not--

00:10:32.445 --> 00:10:33.820
you know, I don't
know if this is

00:10:33.820 --> 00:10:35.280
an actual fact--
people will say,

00:10:35.280 --> 00:10:37.290
like, Asians don't
support each other.

00:10:37.290 --> 00:10:38.880
They don't watch
each other's shows.

00:10:38.880 --> 00:10:41.550
If we make a show or
film about Asian people,

00:10:41.550 --> 00:10:44.230
the numbers, like the
audience, doesn't reflect that.

00:10:44.230 --> 00:10:44.730
Right?

00:10:44.730 --> 00:10:47.800
So on a numbers and
business and industry basis,

00:10:47.800 --> 00:10:50.670
diversity is in my
wheelhouse, in my life,

00:10:50.670 --> 00:10:55.060
every single day in terms of
not just authentic storytelling

00:10:55.060 --> 00:10:57.800
but the business
of the data points.

00:10:57.800 --> 00:10:59.280
Who are the butts in the seats?

00:10:59.280 --> 00:11:00.390
How are we showing up?

00:11:00.390 --> 00:11:03.380
What kind of viewership
are we giving?

00:11:03.380 --> 00:11:06.150
And what does that do for
everybody moving forward

00:11:06.150 --> 00:11:07.710
in terms of getting
other projects--

00:11:07.710 --> 00:11:08.660
other stories-- told?

00:11:08.660 --> 00:11:09.410
DAWN LEE TU: Yeah.

